 For such interaction to be successful, it is often thought that participants
 must be able to recursively model the mental states of others.
 The Canteen Dilemma is an online experiment intended at testing the extend
 to which people actually apply higher order social reasoning.
 The experiment also aims at showing whether there is a learning experience
 within strategic coordination games in terms of applying increasingly higher
 orders of Theory of Mind.
 The experiment might also show whether there exists a discrepancy between
 people's reflection about Theory of Mind and their actual use of it when
 making decisions in games.
 In other words, it might show that even if people possess the mental capability
 to apply 
\emph on
n 
\emph default
degree of Theory of Mind, this capability might not be drawn upon and incorporat
ed successfully into decision processes, as indicated by experiments in
 (Keysar et al.
 2003).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
